Hmm… I love a lot about this, but I do have my nitpicks. The section headers on mobile clip into the sections themselves, obscuring some of the text, and the dividers feel a little cramped because of the minimal padding. There were a couple questionable grammatical/diction choices that probably only bother me, but:



If several days pass without being , SCP-𝕐 consume a number at random, resulting in potential catastrophic consequences for financial, computing, and other mathematics-derivative fields of science.
附加记录：    

This feels like a textbook  mistake.

Ultimately I feel tempted to novote because the ending just doesn't work for me. Re-emphasizing that this thing is an imminent threat feels redundant; I personally would have preferred a technical explanation of some kind of operation the Foundation launches to counter-balance the effect of the meme.

Maybe I'm just turned off by the  format. +1 for everything else, this was otherwise fantastic.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Edit:  Looked through the page source and realized you're importing images from Sandbox 3, which my phone won't display for whatever reason and I'm probably missing some or another stylistic element of this article.





